    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.\n\nIn my code, I would like to have efficient return values and exception tests for simple ctuples.\n```cython\n@cython.exceptval((-1, -1))\ndef test_ctuple_exceptval(fail: cython.bint = False) -> tuple[cython.bint, cython.bint]:\n    \"\"\"\n    >>> test_ctuple_exceptval(fail=False)\n    (True, False)\n    >>> test_ctuple_exceptval(fail=True)\n    Traceback (most recent call last):\n    RuntimeError: FAILED !\n    \"\"\"\n    if fail:\n        raise RuntimeError(\"FAILED !\")\n    return (True, False)\n```\n\n\n### Describe the solution you'd like.\n\nCurrently, this uses a Python tuple as return type but should use a ctuple instead, with the expected exception check.\n\nThe `@exceptval()` decorator even seems redundant and could be used automatically.\n\n### Describe alternatives you've considered.\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
